hint_tooltip = "String Filters can have unique modifiers applied that alter how SPID will apply the filtering to distribution.
Important:
- Unique symbols for the modifiers are automatically applied by the Editor so do NOT include them.

There are 4 different modifiers:
1. Standard:
- Actors MUST match with at least one applied filter to qualify.
- Identified by the lack of any unique symbol.
- Raw Window Appearance: Keyword = NecroDancer|Novice Necromancer, Apprentice Necromancer|NONE|NONE|etc... 

2. Exclusions: 
- Exclude actors that have the Keyword EditorID / Actorbase Name / Actorbase EditorID.
- Identified by the minus symbol '-'
- Raw Window Appearance: Keyword = NotSerana|ActorTypeNPC,-Serana|NONE|NONE|etc...
- Will apply to all npcs that are not Serana.

3. Wildcards:
- Find all actors that have name, editorID or keyword containing the wildcard.
- Identified by the asterisk symbol '*'
- Raw Window Appearance: Keyword = SmellsBad|*Draugr|NONE|NONE|etc...
- Will apply to Draugr Death Lord / Draugr Mage / etc...

4. Linked (Requirements):
- Require actor to have all linked keywords or filter forms to qualify for the filter.
- Identified by the plus symbol '+'
- Raw Window Appearance: e.g. Keyword = SpookyPet|ActorTypeGhost+ActorTypeAnimal|NONE|NONE|etc... 
- Will qualify only ghost animals. It will not include pure animals or ghosts.
- Note: Linked modifiers merge multiple names/keywords/forms into one filter. A unique edit field will unlock when using this modifier."
